.SH TMUX
ZPWR ships a tmux cockpit. Highlights:
.IP \(bu 2
Prefixes default to
.B ZPWR_TMUX_PREFIX_MAC
on Darwin and
.B ZPWR_TMUX_PREFIX_LINUX
on Linux.
.IP \(bu 2
.B "zpwr start"
brings up the cockpit (no extra tabs);
.B "zpwr starttabs"
brings up the full tab set
.RB ( tmm_notabs " / " tmm_full ).
.IP \(bu 2
.BR attach " / " detach
attach to or detach from all sessions.
.IP \(bu 2
Layout snapshots:
.B "zpwr layoutsave"
emits a repeatable script;
.B "zpwr layoutload"
restores it.
.IP \(bu 2
Synced-pane semantics:
.B ZPWR_SEND_KEYS_FULL
controls whether Enter/Control replicate;
.B ZPWR_SEND_KEYS_PANE
activates per-pane targeting.
.B "zpwr startsend / startsendfull / stopsend"
toggle the broadcast.
.IP \(bu 2
.B "zpwr killmux / killremote"
kill the local server / local+remote.
.SH KEYBINDINGS
ZPWR sets up zsh keymaps for
.BR viins ,
.BR vicmd ,
.BR menuselect ,
.BR visual ,
.BR listscroll ,
and
.BR viopp .
Inspect any of them with
.B "bindkey \-M <map> \-l"
or use the search verbs:
.TP
.B zpwr allsearch
Search all keybindings (
.BR zpwrFzfAllKeybind ).
.TP
.B zpwr zshsearch
Search zsh keybindings (
.BR zpwrFzfZshKeybind ).
.TP
.B zpwr vimsearch
Search vim keybindings (
.BR zpwrFzfVimKeybind ).
.PP
The cache files
.IR $ZPWR/zpwrAllKeybindings.txt " and "
.I $ZPWR/zpwrVimKeybindings.txt
back the search; regenerate with
.BR "zpwr regenkeybindings" .
.SH CACHES AND COMPILATION
ZPWR maintains several caches; verbs let you regen, refresh, or wipe them.
.TP
.B .zwc cache
.B "zpwr compile"
recompiles all
.B .zwc
caches;
.B compilefpath
limits to fpath;
.B compilefiles
limits to files;
.B decompile / uncompile
delete them;
.B refreshzwc
delete-then-regen.
.TP
.B compsys cache
.B "zpwr regenzsh"
regenerates the compsys cache to
.BR $ZSH_COMPDUMP ;
.B cleancompcache
clears it.
.TP
.B git repo cache
.B "zpwr regengitrepocache"
and
.B regengitdirtyrepocache
populate
.BR $ZPWR_ALL_GIT_DIRS ;
.BR cleangitcache " / " cleangitcleancache " / " cleangitdirtycache
purge subsets.
.TP
.B env cache
.B "zpwr regenenvcache"
writes
.IR $ZPWR/zpwrEnvKey.txt " and " $ZPWR/zpwrEnvValue.txt ;
.B envcachesearch
queries it via fzf.
.TP
.B ctags / gtags
.B "zpwr regenctags"
writes
.IR ~/tags ;
.B "zpwr regengtags"
runs the same plus GNU global;
.B regengtagspygments
and
.B regengtagstype
choose the parser backend.
.TP
.B history
.B "zpwr regenhistory"
rebuilds
.BR $HISTFILE ;
.BR backuphistory " / " restorehistory
move it sideways.
.TP
.B all-in-one
.B "zpwr regen"
runs all of the above except git-drive search;
.B regenall
also includes that.
.SH LOGGING
.B zpwr
exposes structured log levels that write to
.B $ZPWR_LOGFILE
or to the console.
.TP
.B logdebug ", " logerror ", " loginfo ", " logtrace
Append a log line at the named level to
.BR $ZPWR_LOGFILE .
.TP
.B logdebugconsole ", " logerrorconsole ", " loginfoconsole ", " logtraceconsole
Same levels but to the console (with neon ANSI styling).
.TP
.B taillog ", " logs
Colorized
.B tail
of
.BR $ZPWR_LOGFILE .
.TP
.B cleanlog
Truncate the log.
.PP
Log color is governed by
.BR ZPWR_LOG_DATE_COLOR ", " ZPWR_LOG_MSG_COLOR ", " ZPWR_LOG_QUOTE_COLOR ", " ZPWR_LOG_UNDER_COLOR .
Quote delimiters come from
.BR ZPWR_QUOTE_START_CHAR " / " ZPWR_QUOTE_END_CHAR .
